        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13216.xml">letter from J. V. Carus, 24 June 1881</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD and his son <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1222.xml">Francis Darwin</ref> had started correcting proof-sheets of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref> in May 1881 (see<ref target="./DCP-LETT-13155F.xml"> letter from Francis Darwin, 14 May 1881</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_979.xml">William Clowes &amp; Sons</ref> were printers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3463.xml">John Murray</ref> (1808–92), CD’s publisher.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2758.xml">Ernst Krause</ref> wanted to publish an excerpt from <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref> translated into German in <hi rend="italic">Kosmos</hi> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13158.xml">letter from Ernst Krause, 15 May 1881</ref>). <hi rend="italic">Kosmos</hi> had recently been purchased by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2732.xml">Eduard Koch</ref>, the head of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4246.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">E. Schweizerbart’sche Verlagsbuchhandlung</ref>, CD’s German publisher.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13163.xml">letter to Ernst Krause, 18 May 1881</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f6">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13216.xml">letter from J. V. Carus, 24 June 1881</ref> and n. 4.</note> 
        </div>   
       
